<br>
Personally, I'm in a raiding guild that hands out stacks of dots whenever we need them. For use on both raids and xp groups. If you're raiding, all dots should be paid for by the raid.<br>
<br>
In xp groups... well, if you're normally with a group of friends or guildies, let em know how poor you are and how costly dots are. They should at least reimburse you for all costs, if not help you out further.<br>
<br>
If you do a lot of pick-up groups with strangers (which it sounds like from your description)... Let them know up front that you expect to be compensated for the peridots you use to buff them. If they give you problems or refuse to be fair and help pay... either refuse to buff them or leave the group.<br>
<br>
The method I used a lot was that the cleric gets the first couple of gems (or other sell-to-merchant type loot) that drop for your group. Once you have enough to cover your expected costs, then all loot from then on is distributed evenly.<br>
<br>
Bottom line... You can't be expected to pay to buff your entire group. A good group of nice people should understand this and offer to reimburse your expenses.<br>
<br>
No, I never required payment up front, but then again... I was usually grouped with friends.<br>
<br>
About your sister... well... as you know, not ALL hp buffs use dots. If she was getting a symbol or aego type spell free all the time, she either grouped consistently with friends or with really rich players' alts. In the 3+ years I've been playing a cleric, I don't remember any clerics that paid all dots out of their own pocket unless they were already rich.<br>
<br>
Remember! Be nice about it, but firm... If they won't reimburse you for dots, they don't get buffs! =)<br>
<br>
PS- When I was a young cleric and very poor, I'd only cast the &quot;good hp buffs&quot; on the main tank and the enchanter in the group. Everyone else got a lower buff. Tell the group WHY you're giving them the lower buff (you're too poor!) and many will help. A lot of people just have no clue how much it costs us.<br>
<br>
Tell em straight out:<br>
- 11pp per peridot TIMES 6 players in group = 66pp<br>
- Symbol lasts an hour, so you at least need 66pp per hour that the group hunts together if you're going to break even.<br>
<br>
The formula's a bit better with Temperance I guess, since it lasts longer... It wasn't around when I was a young cleric. =) <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=47567" target="top"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://aledark.free.fr/MorkSig.jpg" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub169.ezboard.com/bmtboards.showUserPublicProfile?gid=morinkhanmt>MorinkhanMT</A> at: 7/25/03 11:44 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub169.ezboard.com/bmtboards.showUserPublicProfile?gid=hidr>hidr</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Qeynos Newbie</span><br>  Posts: 19<br> <font color=#F7DC95>(7/26/03 12:05 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub169.ezboard.com/fmtboardsfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=199.topic&index=2>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://img.villagephotos.com/p/2003-5/205260/fa2183.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_question_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Dots</span><hr size=1> Yes I still do a lot of pick up groups.  I am only lvl 58 so I would say about 50pct are still pick up groups.  I hope as time goes on this well not happen as much.   You had some great advice.  Thank you <p><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.eqfaces.com/photos2/hidrchicknsig.psd.jpg" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub169.ezboard.com/bmtboards.showUserPublicPro