<br>
However, when exp'ing, back when dots were a costly component for me, I was never hesitant to tell the group I wanted reimbursement for them.  I was always lucky, though, in that I got groups who had the ML (master looter) repay me for dots BEFORE the split.  This is the best way to do it.  If everyone in the group gets, say 100pp as the split from loot sold after the group, there's no reason you have to spend the 100 on dots, and they get to bank theirs for savings.  Tell them you used X amount of dots, multiply it times 11, get that amount of pp, and THEN split the total left over.  Don't be nasty about it, of course.  Just explain the situation.  If they are unwilling, toss a Heroic Bond on them, and call it a day <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   Another way to ensure reimbursement is to BE the ML, too. <br>
